Put the peppercorns in a shallow bowl and press the tuna steaks down onto them. Turn the steak over and repeat on the other side.Heat the olive oil in a large frying pan set over a high heat. Sear the tuna for 1â€“2 minutes on each side. Remove the tuna from the pan and set aside to rest. Add the spinach to the pan and cook, stirring, until wilted.Put all the dressing ingredients into a screw-top jar and shake to combine, alternatively, whisk together in a small bowl. Season with salt and pepper.To serve, divide the spinach between two serving plates. Slice the tuna steaks into three, lay on top of the spinach and dress with the ginger and soy dressing.